pub const INTRO_BASE: &str = "Welcome to Off Script! You’re about to play a game of subtle clues, quick thinking, and a little bit of bluffing.\n\nEveryone but one of you has the same prompt.\nOne player — the impostor — has something different.\n\nTake turns asking questions about the prompt.\nAfter each question, everyone else gives an answer. Keep things natural — don’t reveal too much.\n\nIf you have the real prompt, your goal is to spot who doesn’t quite fit.\nIf you’re the impostor, your goal is to blend in and figure out what everyone else is talking about.\n\nOnce everyone has asked a question, vote on who you think the impostor is.\n\nStay subtle. Stay convincing.\nAnd whatever you do… don’t go off script.";

pub const BOT_INTRO_BASE: &str = "Game: Off Script. There are N players, and one player is randomly assigned as the impostor. All other players receive the same prompt, while the impostor receives a different but related prompt. The game proceeds in a round where each player takes a turn asking one question about the prompt, and after each question, all other players provide an answer based on their own prompt. Players should answer in a way that is truthful but indirect, avoiding explicitly revealing the prompt. Questions should be designed to subtly test for shared understanding without making the prompt obvious. After every player has asked exactly one question, the round ends and all players vote on who they believe the impostor is. Non-impostors should aim to ask targeted, discriminative questions and watch for inconsistencies in others’ answers. The impostor should aim to give flexible, non-committal answers, adapt to emerging patterns in the conversation, and gradually infer the true prompt while avoiding drawing suspicion.";
